cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.IR 

The paper deals with computer vision and machine learning techniques for recognizing colorectal tumors in endoscopic images. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also uses convolutional neural networks (CNN) and linear SVM classifiers, which are common techniques in machine learning, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also deals with medical imaging, which could place it in cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
